# Language

Semantic primes, schemas, structural rules, morphology, music, therapy.


## Schemas = Bond Patterns = Innate Seed

16 bond patterns (2^4) map 1:1 to Lakoff/Mandler image schemas — the
pre-verbal concepts humans are born with:

  identity=IDENTITY, π=FORCE, ∘=PATH, π+∘=TRAVERSAL, ∮=CYCLE,
  π+∮=FULL-EMPTY, π+δ=CONTACT, ∘+∮+δ=BALANCE, π+∘+∮+δ=CONTAINER

An infant experiences FORCE (womb), CYCLE (heartbeat), FULL-EMPTY
(hunger), CONTACT (touch), CONTAINER (own body) — all before language.
~24 schemas reduce to 16 irreducible patterns (extras are magnitude
variants, compositions, or inverses).


## Three-Layer Seed

  Layer 0: bonds/schemas (16, innate, hardcoded, never changes)
  Layer 1: primes/first words (65 NSM, learned year 1, anchored to schemas)
  Layer 2: full vocabulary (memetic, context-learned, infinite)

Same as generations: Gen1=values, Gen2=operations, Gen3=patterns.
The equation already has the seed. The intelligence doesn't need a
separate "model" — the equation IS the model.


