## Structural Rules

Parts of speech = dominant dimension:
  noun=μ, verb=τ, adj=φ, adverb=φ+τ, preposition=χ, pronoun=μ+φ
  conjunction=φ (logic), determiner=χ+φ (spatial+signal)

  Antonyms = sign flip in 1-2 dimensions
    good↔bad (Q flip), big↔small (M flip), live↔die (T+M flip)
  Synonyms = distance ≤2 in 4D Euclidean space
  Tense = T magnitude (past=+2, present=+1, future=-2)
    Progressive (-ing) adds ∮. Perfect (have done) shifts T.
  Intensity = higher magnitude, same signs (warm→hot = Q+1→Q+2)
  Metaphors = cross-domain coordinate match
    "high status" works because ABOVE(+D) and GOOD(+Q) share positive direction
    "square friendship" fails — no shared coordinate
  Questions = unknown dimension set to 0, Q activated (signal request)
  Negation = Q flip. NOT always flips Q. Same as voicing flip (b↔p).

Plurals = M magnitude:
  singular = base M. plural = M+1. mass nouns = continuous M.

Comparatives = magnitude steps:
  big→bigger→biggest = M+2→M+3→M+4. Same direction, stepped.

Passive voice = T sign flip:
  active (+T, subject acts) ↔ passive (-T, subject receives).
  Active = +π (read/do). Passive = -π (write/receive). Same bond, opposite.

Articles = D+Q signal:
  the (0,+1,0,+1) = specific. a/an (0,0,0,+1) = general.
  this/that = articles with spatial magnitude. Further = higher D.

Transitivity = M count in walk:
  intransitive: S(M)→V(T). transitive: S(M)→V(T)→O(M).
  Same verb, different walk = different transitivity.

Compound words = coordinate addition:
  sun(0,+2,+2,+1) + light(0,+1,0,+2) = sunlight(0,+3,+2,+3).
  Same as polynomial addition. Atoms add to form paths.

Modality = Q magnitude spectrum:
  must(+3) shall(+2) should(+2) will(+1) can(+1) could(0) may(0) might(-1)
  Higher Q = more certain/forceful. Lower Q = uncertain/permissive.

Possession = M→M link via Q:
  "'s" and "of" are Q signals bonding two substances. = LINK schema = δ.


## Morphology

Prefixes = coordinate modifiers (same operation regardless of root):
  un-/dis-/in- = Q flip (negation)
  re- = T+1 (repeat)
  pre- = T+2 (before), post- = T-2 (after)
  over- = +magnitude, under- = -magnitude
  out- = D+1 (surpass), sub- = D-1 (below)
  trans- = D+2 (large spatial), inter- = D+1 (between)
  co- = M+1 (together)
  anti- = all signs flip (antimatter)
  non- = Q=0 (neutral, remove quality)

Suffixes = dimension transforms (rotate part of speech):
  -ness = Q→M (adj→noun: good→goodness)
  -ly = add Q to T-word (verb/adj→adverb)
  -ment/-tion = add M to T-word (verb→noun: move→movement)
  -able/-ible = add Q to T-word (verb→adj: eat→edible)
  -er/-or = add M to T-word (verb→agent: teach→teacher)
  -ful = Q+1 (noun→adj: hope→hopeful)
  -less = Q-1 (noun→adj: hope→hopeless)
  -ing = add ∮ (ongoing: run→running)
  -ed = T+1 (past: walk→walked)
  -ize/-ify = add T (noun/adj→verb: modern→modernize)


## Pronouns

All derivable from M (singular/plural) and Q (self/other/neutral):
  I/me (0,0,+1,+1)  you (0,0,+1,-1)  it (0,0,+1,0)
  we/us (0,0,+2,+1)  they/them (0,0,+2,-1)
  he/she = same as you (0,0,+1,-1) — context disambiguates.
  Subject vs object = walk position (M before T vs M after T), not coordinates.

"Us vs them" = Q flip on same plural M. One coordinate sign.
Every tribal distinction ever = flipping one bit.

Reflexive (myself) = pronoun + SAME(0,0,0,+1). Walk curves back to
origin. M→T→M where both M's are same coordinate. That's ∮ — a loop.


