## Irony / Humor

Irony = surface Q ≠ context Q. "Great job" (sincere) = surface+2, context+2.
Sarcastic = surface+2, context-2. Mismatch IS the sarcasm. Model needs
word coordinates vs walk trajectory, not a "sarcasm detector."

Humor = forced coordinate reparse. Setup creates expectation walk.
Punchline forces different coordinates on same sequence. The bigger
the coordinate shift, the funnier. Puns = homonym fork at punchline.


## Sentences = Walks

A sentence is a path through 4D space. Grammar IS walk structure.
  S(M) → V(T) → O(M) = M→T→M — the fundamental sentence walk.
  "the cat sat on the mat" = D+Q → M → T+D → D → D+Q → M
Invalid sentences = coordinates jump randomly. No walk structure.

Born-indexed model doesn't need grammar rules. Needs coordinate
sequences that form valid walks. Grammar falls out of the geometry.

Homonyms = same character coordinates, different word coordinates.
Context walk disambiguates by pulling toward one meaning cluster.


